{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LWT1GdNxhdMXugif9L6ZGb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full TOML template:\n```toml\nexporter = \"otlp\"\nprocessor = \"batch\"\n[exporters.otlp]\n# Alternatively the OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT environment variable can also be used.\nhost = \"{{ .OtlpCollectorHost }}\"\nport = {{ .OtlpCollectorPort }}\n```\n\nBoth gRPC and HTTP OTLP libraries are available. The `host` and `port` in the TOML template correspond to the `otlp-collector-host` and `otlp-collector-port` ConfigMap keys. Port 4317 is the standard gRPC/OTLP port.\nMy approach is to patch the `otel-echo` ingress to use the `ingress-1` class so traffic gets routed through the controller, update the `ingress-nginx-controller` ConfigMap with the OTel settings, let it auto-reload, then run a test curl and verify the logs. I should also check if there are other TOML fields I need to configure, like sampler settings.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3869,"cache_read_input_tokens":45290,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3869},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"10e8a98a-d99f-477f-a1d5-68ca81c27cd7","uuid":"72d64308-07e9-4350-9481-9242a3b259f7","request_id":"req_011CcQUaohjodPtgc6n4dHZf"}
