{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NtE7CSHxFCfF4BWWgFB4kK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working end-to-end. The OTel collector received the trace with ID `53890a9e99473ab230af0180e0d4822a` (matching the access log) and the target `/otel-check`.\n\nHere's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem:** The `otel-echo` ingress used class `nginx` but the active controller in `ingress-nginx` namespace serves class `ingress-1` — so the controller ignored the ingress and OTel was not configured.\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **Fixed ingress routing** — patched `demo/otel-echo` ingress to use `ingressClassName: ingress-1` so the active controller picks it up.\n\n2. **Enabled OpenTelemetry** — patched the `ingress-nginx-controller` ConfigMap with:\n   - `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` — loads `otel_ngx_module.so` and generates the TOML config\n   - `otlp-collector-host: \"otel-collector.otel.svc\"` + `otlp-collector-port: \"4317\"` — points to the existing collector\n   - `otel-sampler: \"AlwaysOn\"` + `otel-sampler-ratio: \"1.0\"` — 100% sampling\n   - `otel-service-name: \"nginx-ingress\"` — service name in traces\n\n3. **Updated log format** — set `log-format-upstream` to include `otel_trace_id=$opentelemetry_trace_id otel_span_id=$opentelemetry_span_id`\n\nThe controller auto-reloaded nginx, and the `/otel-check` request now produces a log entry with non-empty trace and span IDs, with traces exported to the OTel collector."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":318,"cache_read_input_tokens":59113,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":318},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"10e8a98a-d99f-477f-a1d5-68ca81c27cd7","uuid":"dd688b8f-bf65-4b00-bba6-46c